<item>
            <title>[MJAVADOC-2] Plugin should be configured in &lt;reporting&gt; not &lt;build&gt;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MJAVADOC-2</link>
                <project id="12317529" key="MJAVADOC">Maven Javadoc Plugin (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The documentation at&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-javadoc-plugin/configuration.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maven.apache.org/plugins/maven-javadoc-plugin/configuration.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;indicates that you configure this plugin inside the &amp;lt;build&amp;gt; element of the pom; some research revealed that it is part of the &amp;lt;reporting&amp;gt; element. As a new Maven (2) user, this really caught me unawares.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>window xp, jdk 1.5, cygwin</environment>
        <key id="12804204">MJAVADOC-2</key>
            <summary>Plugin should be configured in &lt;reporting&gt; not &lt;build&gt;</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
