                                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14438654" author="indrajitr" created="Sun, 18 Dec 2005 00:49:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Javadoc plugin config inside &lt;tt&gt;&amp;lt;build&amp;gt;...&amp;lt;/build&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; isn&apos;t honored when javadoc is generated as part of &lt;tt&gt;site:site&lt;/tt&gt; but it is honored by &lt;tt&gt;javadoc:javadoc&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See a related issue MNG-1857.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438757" author="brettporter" created="Mon, 19 Dec 2005 00:39:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;need to determine the best way to document this, and remove the misleading section in the javadoc plugin.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;reporting&amp;gt; - always used, for general report settings&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;build&amp;gt; - used when run in the build lifecycle (for stuff not related to generating the site, eg clover:check might set a failure attribute)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14438635" author="mperham" created="Tue, 10 Jan 2006 12:14:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the docs with examples for both scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17957377" author="olamy" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2025 01:16:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/olamy/maven-javadoc-plugin/issues/395&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;olamy/maven-javadoc-plugin#395&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
